Subject: Re: [T2] shock bushing lube

On Wed, 25 Apr 2007, Dave C. Bolen wrote:

> Guys,
>
> The front shock bushings on my 78 are squeeking, especially in the cool
> mornings.
>
> What is best for these...silicone lube? or something better...or will
> the silicone eat the rubber in the bushings?

First, make sure that it isn't the trailing arm bearings that are
squeaking.  Grease them until you make a mess!

Your shock bushing do not swivel.  What little movement they have is taken
up by the rubber bushing.  If they squeak a little graphite should fix
things.


George
